Manchester United have confirmed that new signing Amad Diallo will be the club’s new No.19. Diallo finally completed his transfer from Atalanta to United this week, joining for an initial fee of £18million plus significant add-ons. The Ivorian joins up with Ole Gunnar Solskjaer’s side having made his name as a talented young winger in Italy. United have now revealed the 18-year-old will wear the No.19, previously worn by Marcus Rashford, Danny Welbeck and Dwight Yorke, among others at Old Trafford. He will also have his first name ‘Amad’ on the back, having legally changed his surname from Traore to Diallo last September. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Others to have worn the No.19 at united include goalkeeper Edwin van der Sar, Ronny Johnsen, another goalkeeper in Ricardo, Eric Djemba-Djemba, Gerard Pique and James Wilson. Diallo wore No.79 at Atalanta. “I think he will do well but it important to keep calm with him. He’s a top man. I speak with him and speak with the family. Now the guy is very happy to sign for Manchester United. Everybody waits for him and that’s it.”